    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-11T07:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-11T07:35:00-05:00" n="604"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">391.1164/120: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-11T16:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 11, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 11—2:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>163. I called with Dodds, Hutchins and Allen<note n="7" xml:id="d604fn7">Cady H.
                        Allen, of the Presbyterian Mission at Hamadan, Iran.</note> on the Minister
                    of Foreign Affairs this morning and referred to my note of October 13<note n="8"
                        xml:id="d604fn8">See telegram No. 50, October 11, noon, to the Chargé in
                        Iran, <ref target="#pg_534">p. 534</ref>.</note>
                    <pb facs="0543" n="537" xml:id="pg_537"/> (see my despatch No. 1705).<note n="9"
                        xml:id="d604fn9">Not printed.</note> He was very cordial and seemed
                    impressed by the fact that representations [<hi rend="italic"
                        >representative</hi>] had been sent all the way from America. He said
                    nothing that would indicate the slightest change in the Government’s decision to
                    proceed with the expropriation of the schools.</p>
                <p>I shall also introduce the negotiations [<hi rend="italic">negotiators</hi>] to
                    the Prime Minister and to the Minister of Education.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
